<TITLE> Govt resets school schedules </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 24 (bdnews24.com)  The government has reset class schedules of all government and non-government schools, colleges and madrasas, according to a statement made Sunday. In line with the new schedule, classes at single-shift institutions will be held 8am-1pm from March to August and 10am-4pm from September to February. In two-shift secondary schools or madrasas, the morning shift will begin at 7am and finish at 12pm while the day shift will begin at 12.15pm and finish at 5.25pm, according to the statement by the government. bdn
